ValueSet

Expansion performed internally based on codesystem IPS.HAJJ.CONSENT CodeSystem v2.0.3 (CodeSystem)

This value set contains 4 concepts

CodeSystemDisplay (en-US)Definition
  CONSENT-KSAhttp://smart.who.int/ips-pilgrimage/CodeSystem/IPS.HAJJ.CONSENTConsent for Kingdom of Saudi Arabia

The Pilgrim consents to share his-her International Patient Summary (IPS data) during the provision of clinical care at Ministry of Health-Saudi Arabia in Haj District area healthcare facilities through the Hajj-1446/2025 event as any follow up care that might be needed from any healthcare practitioners

  CONSENT-IDNhttp://smart.who.int/ips-pilgrimage/CodeSystem/IPS.HAJJ.CONSENTConsent for Indonesia

<INSERT TEXT FROM INDONESIA: discuss pilgrims's consent to utilize Satusehat to enable access to KSA to their IPS if they are in need of care during Hajj>

  CONSENT-MYShttp://smart.who.int/ips-pilgrimage/CodeSystem/IPS.HAJJ.CONSENTConsent for Malaysia

The Malaysian Hajj pilgrim has provided consent for sharing the International Patient Summary (IPS) generated from the data recorded during the Hajj pilgrim health examination, as well as the vaccination records stored on MySejahtera to Kingdom of Saudi Arabia

  CONSENT-OMNhttp://smart.who.int/ips-pilgrimage/CodeSystem/IPS.HAJJ.CONSENTConsent for Oman

<INSERT TEXT FROM OMAN: discuss pilgrims's consent to utilize Oman's e-Health Portal to enable access to KSA to their IPS if they are in need of care>

contains.display: Consent for Kingdom of Saudi Arabia
